Class WriteOnlyStorageException

Object
Throwable
Exception
DataStoreException
WriteOnlyStorageException
All Implemented Interfaces:
Serializable, Localized­Exception
public class WriteOnlyStorageException extends DataStoreException
Thrown when a Data­Store cannot perform a read operation. This exception may happen if the Channel used by a data store implements Writable­Byte­Channel only, without implementing also Readable­Byte­Channel.
Since:
1.5
